---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Meet Jacob Gordon — owner-operator of Gordon Concrete Pumping. BS Concrete Industry Management student at Texas State University with hands-on industry experience across ready mix, QC, and aggregate operations."
>

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Owner-Operated</span>
      <h1>Meet Jacob Gordon</h1>
      <p>Concrete isn't just a job — it's a degree, a career track, and now a business.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro-grid">
        <div class="intro-text">
          <span class="section-label">About Jacob</span>
          <h2>Not Just an Operator — A Concrete Professional</h2>
          <p>
            Gordon Concrete Pumping is owned and operated by Jacob Gordon, a Concrete Industry Management
            student at Texas State University and a working concrete professional with hands-on experience
            across ready mix operations, quality control, and aggregate engineering.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most boom pump operators drive a truck. Jacob understands the material going through it.
            That background — from batching plant operations to jobsite field testing — means he brings
            more than just reach to your pour. He understands mix designs, placement requirements,
            and what makes a pour go right or wrong.
          </p>
          <p>
            Based in Rockwall, TX, Jacob operates one 38-meter truck-mounted boom pump across the
            DFW Metroplex and Tyler corridor — doing every job himself, personally.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="intro-credentials">
          <div class="credential-card">
            <div class="cred-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M4.26 10.147a60.436 60.436 0 00-.491 6.347A48.627 48.627 0 0112 20.904a48.627 48.627 0 018.232-4.41 60.46 60.46 0 00-.491-6.347m-15.482 0a50.57 50.57 0 00-2.658-.813A59.905 59.905 0 0112 3.493a59.902 59.902 0 0110.399 5.84c-.896.248-1.783.52-2.658.814m-15.482 0A50.697 50.697 0 0112 13.489a50.702 50.702 0 017.74-3.342M6.75 15a.75.75 0 100-1.5.75.75 0 000 1.5zm0 0v-3.675A55.378 55.378 0 0112 8.443m-7.007 11.55A5.981 5.981 0 006.75 15.75v-1.5"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <strong>BS Concrete Industry Management</strong>
              <span>Texas State University</span>
              <span class="cred-note">Expected May 2026 — one of the few dedicated concrete degrees in the US</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="credential-card">
            <div class="cred-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 21h16.5M4.5 3h15M5.25 3v18m13.5-18v18M9 6.75h1.5m-1.5 3h1.5m-1.5 3h1.5m3-6H15m-1.5 3H15m-1.5 3H15M9 21v-3.375c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h3.75c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125V21"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Industry Experience</strong>
              <span>Heidelberg Materials, Centex Materials</span>
              <span class="cred-note">Operations, QC, and aggregate roles across Texas</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="credential-card">
            <div class="cred-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 10.5a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 10.5c0 7.142-7.5 11.25-7.5 11.25S4.5 17.642 4.5 10.5a7.5 7.5 0 1115 0z"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Based in Rockwall, TX</strong>
              <span>Dallas–Tyler Corridor</span>
              <span class="cred-note">Centrally located for DFW and East Texas jobs</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="credential-card">
            <div class="cred-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 6.75c0 8.284 6.716 15 15 15h2.25a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-1.372c0-.516-.351-.966-.852-1.091l-4.423-1.106c-.44-.11-.902.055-1.173.417l-.97 1.293c-.282.376-.769.542-1.21.38a12.035 12.035 0 01-7.143-7.143c-.162-.441.004-.928.38-1.21l1.293-.97c.363-.271.527-.734.417-1.173L6.963 3.102a1.125 1.125 0 00-1.091-.852H4.5A2.25 2.25 0 002.25 4.5v2.25z"/></svg></div>
            <div>
              <strong>Owner on Every Job</strong>
              <span>No dispatchers, no subcontractors</span>
              <span class="cred-note">Call Jacob directly — (469) 704-4227</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Education — Highlighted -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Education</span>
        <h2>Degree Built for This Industry</h2>
        <p>The BS in Concrete Industry Management is one of the most specialised construction degrees available in the United States.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="edu-feature">
        <div class="edu-feature-header">
          <div class="edu-logo-placeholder">TSU</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Texas State University</h3>
            <p class="edu-location">San Marcos, TX</p>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-dates">Aug 2023 – May 2026</div>
        </div>

        <div class="edu-degree">
          <div class="edu-degree-badge">Bachelor of Science</div>
          <h4>Concrete Industry Management</h4>
          <p>
            The CIM program at Texas State is one of only a handful in the country dedicated entirely
            to the concrete industry. The curriculum covers mix design, materials science, construction
            management, quality control, and industry operations — making graduates uniquely qualified
            to work across the full concrete supply chain.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="edu-highlights-grid">
          <div class="edu-highlight">
            <h5>Materials Science & Mix Design</h5>
            <p>Deep understanding of concrete properties, admixtures, aggregate selection, and how mix design affects pumpability and placement.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-highlight">
            <h5>Quality Control & Testing</h5>
            <p>Formal training in concrete testing methods — slump, air content, compressive strength, and field testing procedures used on real job sites.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-highlight">
            <h5>Construction Operations</h5>
            <p>Project management, site logistics, and the operational side of large-scale concrete construction — not just the material itself.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-highlight">
            <h5>Industry Connections</h5>
            <p>The CIM program has direct ties to major industry players — Heidelberg Materials, Vulcan, CEMEX — giving graduates a professional network from day one.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lab-instructor-callout">
          <div class="lic-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="28" height="28" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.75 3.104v5.714a2.25 2.25 0 01-.659 1.591L5 14.5M9.75 3.104c-.251.023-.501.05-.75.082m.75-.082a24.301 24.301 0 014.5 0m0 0v5.714c0 .597.237 1.17.659 1.591L19.8 15.3M14.25 3.104c.251.023.501.05.75.082M19.8 15.3l-1.57.393A9.065 9.065 0 0112 15a9.065 9.065 0 00-6.23-.693L5 14.5m14.8.8l1.402 1.402c1.232 1.232.65 3.318-1.067 3.611A48.309 48.309 0 0112 21a48.309 48.309 0 01-8.135-.687c-1.718-.293-2.3-2.379-1.067-3.61L5 14.5"/></svg></div>
          <div>
            <strong>Lab Instructor — CIM 3420: Properties and Testing</strong>
            <p>
              Currently teaching the Properties and Testing course at Texas State University (Aug 2025–Present),
              managing 25 students in preparation for the <strong>ACI Field Grade I Exam</strong> — the industry
              standard certification for concrete field testing personnel.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Experience -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Industry Experience</span>
        <h2>Worked Every Side of the Industry</h2>
        <p>From the batch plant to the job site — Jacob has worked across operations, quality control, and materials sourcing.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="experience-timeline">

        <div class="exp-item">
          <div class="exp-marker">
            <div class="exp-dot"></div>
            <div class="exp-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-header">
              <div>
                <h4>Ready Mix Intern — Operations</h4>
                <span class="exp-company">Heidelberg Materials | Houston, TX</span>
              </div>
              <span class="exp-dates">May – Aug 2025</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="exp-bullets">
              <li>Managed day-to-day RMC plant operations; batched concrete using CommandBatch software</li>
              <li>Responsible for daily KPI tracking, mid-month and EOM inventory, daily reports, and weekly safety meetings</li>
              <li>Participated in the Command Alkon RemoteBatch trial run</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="exp-tag">Heidelberg Materials — one of the world's largest building materials companies</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="exp-item">
          <div class="exp-marker">
            <div class="exp-dot"></div>
            <div class="exp-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-header">
              <div>
                <h4>Ready Mix Intern — Quality Control</h4>
                <span class="exp-company">Centex Materials | Austin, TX</span>
              </div>
              <span class="exp-dates">Dec 2024 – May 2025</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="exp-bullets">
              <li>Extensive jobsite field testing of fresh and hardened concrete properties</li>
              <li>Involved in TxDOT trial batch testing — Texas Department of Transportation approval process</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="exp-tag">QC field experience on active Texas construction sites</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="exp-item">
          <div class="exp-marker">
            <div class="exp-dot"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="exp-content">
            <div class="exp-header">
              <div>
                <h4>Aggregate Engineering Intern</h4>
                <span class="exp-company">Heidelberg Materials | Ennis, TX</span>
              </div>
              <span class="exp-dates">May – Aug 2024</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="exp-bullets">
              <li>Learned sand and gravel operations from the ground up — quarrying, processing, and supply</li>
              <li>Understanding of aggregate quality and its downstream impact on concrete performance</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="exp-tag">Raw materials — where concrete quality starts</div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why It Matters -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="why-matters-block">
        <div class="wm-text">
          <span class="section-label">Why It Matters to You</span>
          <h2>What This Background Means on Your Job</h2>
          <p>
            When you hire a concrete pump operator, you're hiring someone to place your material correctly.
            Jacob's background means he's not guessing — he understands mix design, pumpability,
            placement technique, and what the concrete is doing as it comes out of the boom.
          </p>
          <p>
            If there's a slump issue, a blockage risk, or a placement timing question on your job,
            you want someone who's been in the QC lab and on the batch plant — not just behind the wheel.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="wm-points">
          <div class="wm-point">
            <span class="wm-check">✓</span>
            <span>Understands mix design and how it affects pumpability</span>
          </div>
          <div class="wm-point">
            <span class="wm-check">✓</span>
            <span>Trained in ACI field testing — knows what good concrete looks like</span>
          </div>
          <div class="wm-point">
            <span class="wm-check">✓</span>
            <span>Operations background — understands the logistics of a concrete pour</span>
          </div>
          <div class="wm-point">
            <span class="wm-check">✓</span>
            <span>Industry relationships across DFW and Texas concrete supply chain</span>
          </div>
          <div class="wm-point">
            <span class="wm-check">✓</span>
            <span>Dedicated degree in concrete — not a general construction background</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-banner">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Work With Jacob?</h2>
      <p>Get in touch directly — every job is run by the owner.</p>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Quote</a>
        <a href="tel:+14697044227" class="btn btn-outline">Call (469) 704-4227</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Intro */
  .intro-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .intro-text h2 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .intro-credentials {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .credential-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }

  .cred-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .credential-card strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.1rem;
  }

  .credential-card span {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .cred-note {
    font-size: 0.78rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }

  /* Education Feature */
  .edu-feature {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .edu-feature-header {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .edu-logo-placeholder {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    width: 52px;
    height: 52px;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .edu-feature-header h3 {
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
  }

  .edu-location {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .edu-dates {
    margin-left: auto;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .edu-degree {
    padding: 2rem 2rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .edu-degree-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #e8f0fe;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.7rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .edu-degree h4 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .edu-degree p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .edu-highlights-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .edu-highlight {
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .edu-highlight:nth-child(even) { border-right: none; }
  .edu-highlight:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: none; }

  .edu-highlight h5 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .edu-highlight p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .lab-instructor-callout {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    background: #fff8ed;
    border-top: 1px solid #ffe4b2;
  }

  .lic-icon { font-size: 1.75rem; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .lab-instructor-callout strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .lab-instructor-callout p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Experience Timeline */
  .experience-timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .exp-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .exp-marker {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 0.3rem;
  }

  .exp-dot {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    border: 2px solid #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .exp-line {
    width: 2px;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--color-border);
    min-height: 40px;
    margin-top: 6px;
  }

  .exp-content {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    flex: 1;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }

  .exp-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .exp-header h4 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .exp-company {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .exp-dates {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    white-space: nowrap;
    background: #fff8ed;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.7rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
  }

  .exp-bullets {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }

  .exp-bullets li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .exp-bullets li::before {
    content: '→';
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .exp-tag {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: 0.6rem;
  }

  /* Why It Matters */
  .why-matters-block {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 3rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
  }

  .wm-text h2 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .wm-points {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }

  .wm-point {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .wm-check {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    width: 22px;
    height: 22px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 1px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .intro-grid,
    .why-matters-block { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .edu-highlights-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .edu-highlight { border-right: none !important; }
    .edu-feature-header { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
    .edu-dates { margin-left: 0; }
  }
</style>
